result.name: Tam Jai Yunnan Noodles

reviews.text: I love this noodle. Reasonable price and delicious food.
Seating was comfortable enough. Waitress take order promptly and food was delivered fast. The beef could be more tender. Chicken wings are good. Met my expectation for a fast convenient lunch.
Very cheap, less 40hkd for a huge bowl of noodles. Food is quite good, I love their Si Chuan chicken. They dont speak much English 😅
Food was slightly more salty than our liking. Service from staff was prompt. Environment was cleaner than those cha chaan teng.

This is my 2nd visit to Tam Chai Noodle. We went here for dinner after going to HK museum of history. Located just across the premise. The place is clean, spacious than their branch in Shatin.

At the time of my visit I was served with one of the friendlier waitress, and able to speak english. We ordered non spicy broth for kids and the Mala (Szechuan peppercorn) for me & wife. Their menu have english translation.

The noodle have slick textures like spaghetti but a little bit chewy. The original broth is delicious but we really like the spicy broth since we both like the flavor & aroma of the Szechuan peppercorn. I recommend to try the least spicy if you've never taste Mala before, since the flavor might not be for everyone.
